and acts faster.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.R83oLIyzHG3EaLoh]{Hologram Memory}</strong>&nbsp;Extract a creature's memory and replay it as a hologram.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.8FNA793CY1hNWUEP]{Id Insinuation}&nbsp;</strong>By invading targets with your psychic presence, you isolate parts of their minds, preventing them from functioning in a coherent manner.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.3unsFniXAJCoerPr]{Intellect Fortress}&nbsp;</strong>When you or a creature within range is subjected to a mind‑affecting effect while this spell is active, you disrupt it with the power of pure logic.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.vOQ1NkfDHafdqTfE]{Irradiate}</strong>&nbsp;Flood area with dangerous radiation.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.dNNUCRXmCtrucIKf]{Mental Block}&nbsp;</strong>Cause creatures to forget how to use their feats and abilities</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.qZwiwVn1VdlTX71E]{Meticulous Match}&nbsp;</strong>You compare two similar items and know if they are identical to one another or not.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.XGi2g9pQwzebQtHR]{Mind of Three} </strong>You split your mind, retaining your normal consciousness but gaining two other personas.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.7XJ6x5BZv1k1eBBz]{Mind Thrust}</strong>&nbsp;Mentally deal 7d10 damage to one target.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.nffP8Mq7rJ8Rskb9]{Mystic Cure}</strong>&nbsp;Restore 5d8 + your Wisdom modifier Hit Points to a living creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.mNHdfIKpF11fhEjo]{Necromantic Revitalization}&nbsp;</strong>Restore hit points to an undead creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.BadW8vaiF813YRw1]{Nightmare}&nbsp;</strong>Send a terrible nightmare to a distant target.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.e6iK8NCKZTNkDffh]{Pinpoint Navigation}&nbsp;</strong>Gain +10 to Piloting checks for navigation.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.wB957SDHp5jkTR4F]{Polar Vortex}&nbsp;</strong>You generate an arctic storm of harsh winds and battering hail and snow.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.gNgdSyi4pXQmasmc]{Polymorph}&nbsp;</strong>Change the target's shape into that of another creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.OHGWvzUb9MJCNB8u]{Psychokinetic Strangulation}</strong>&nbsp;Concentrate to immobilize target and deal 3d8 damage per round.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.oCZRtcoaUZKR1eSo]{Ray of Exhaustion}</strong>&nbsp;Ray makes target @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.33ynSbmexuxC3cAQ]{Exhausted}.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.YGkyMwEE6SLfZc4r]{Remove Affliction}</strong>&nbsp;Neutralize curses, @Compendium[sfrpg.rules.GnEF27Oot3zqTaBQ]{Diseases}, infestations, @Compendium[sfrpg.rules.aKqRtg165rAly1Cc]{Poisons}, and other harmful conditions affecting a creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.nsrp5apjB7X8aOgV]{Resistant Armor, Lesser}</strong>&nbsp;Grant DR 5/&mdash; or energy resistance 5 against two energy types.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.rGR9lLmVNHHu0zVZ]{Shifting Shadows}</strong> Shadows make it harder to tell friend from foe.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.4prroV3z26u1cy5y]{Slow}</strong>&nbsp;One creature per level moves and acts slower.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.SLwl3LWEm2DyzNc4]{Speak with Dead}</strong>&nbsp;Corpse answers up to six questions.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.nmBeoZQUNcZw7nmy]{Suggestion}</strong>&nbsp;Compel a target to follow stated course of action.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.rJ0acpj21GDJYaim]{Summon Creature}&nbsp;</strong>This spell summons an extraplanar creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.rHscFpMmXkZOOkgV]{Synaptic Pulse}</strong>&nbsp;Stun all creatures within 20 feet for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.uWKhr01bnKxuNRkL]{Tongues}</strong>&nbsp;Target can speak and understand any language.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.G5BCE1kbpOj1mwiq]{Umbral Tendrils}&nbsp;</strong>Assault a group of creatures with shadowy tentacles.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.XBuEMnUgarrcM5qk]{Viral Destruction}&nbsp;</strong>Create a virus in a recently @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.nEJIWMKbPjqKuelo]{Dead} body, allowing it to strike again and potentially spread the virus further.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>4th-Level</h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.tDS3tcN5yD0Y9D52]{Animate Dead}</strong>&nbsp;Create controlled undead creatures out of target corpses.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.kzOemsOWuqgbbGZw]{Baleful Polymorph}&nbsp;</strong>Change the target's shape to that of a smaller, weaker creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.11X6d8ptU5SKMUQ0]{Baleful Polymorph, Mass}&nbsp;</strong>Change multiple targets' shapes to that of a smaller, weaker creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.BQHFi2CRH4LnowYb]{Borrow Corruption}&nbsp;</strong>Gain the benefits of a corruption from someone else.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.wSeE9HyAmM7lTdpo]{Confusion}</strong>&nbsp;Targets behave randomly for 1 round per level.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.FTBjUT3rg3Rosn8l]{Control Atmosphere}&nbsp;</strong>Alter the corrosiveness, density, or toxicity of the surrounding atmosphere</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.yqMZTZSiV3hPIRr6]{Cosmic Eddy}</strong>&nbsp;Whirlwind deals 4d6 damage and knocks creatures @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.XeRGqHVtcZ7vsgJ0]{Prone}.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.QtZHSuJf0hcryYtR]{Death Ward}</strong>&nbsp;Target gains +4 bonus to saves against death spells, and is immune to negative energy and gaining negative levels.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.3us1YJn4pQg6QEc1]{Dimensional Anchor}&nbsp;</strong>Prevent a target from leaving the plane.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.7HZVlS48z55YO78b]{Discern Lies}</strong>&nbsp;Reveal deliberate falsehoods.</p>\n<p><strong>Dismissal:</strong> Force a creature to return to its native plane.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.JDB8BExJpNT04wUz]{Displace Memory}&nbsp;</strong>You deposit a memory into a small object.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.APgLb0BS0VgtE06l]{Divination}</strong>&nbsp;Gain useful advice for specific proposed actions.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.CO9wzmYbZjeijJUc]{Ectoplasmic Eruption}&nbsp;</strong>Swirling psychic matter, known as ectoplasm, erupts from a point you choose.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.wQBbe1s9VYVm5vGG]{Enervation}</strong>&nbsp;Ray imposes 2 negative levels.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.zZGvuXQErBrHqyS6]{Fear}</strong>&nbsp;All targets within a cone are @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.BVdjvpucmvQU4cc1]{Panicked} for 1 minute.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.y07M0jd1sVw4uRPh]{Gravity Well}&nbsp;</strong>Create a point of high gravity that knocks creatures in the area @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.XeRGqHVtcZ7vsgJ0]{Prone} and pulls them closer to the center.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.sI0dGecvFmVOPPhn]{Hold Monster}</strong>&nbsp;Paralyze one creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.UQYaZbfgch9AGnJJ]{Miasma}&nbsp;</strong>Create air that sickens those who breathe it.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.Yw8a8A1rjbLXkcpr]{Mind Probe}</strong>&nbsp;Potentially access a target creature's memories and its knowledge.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.7XJ6x5BZv1k1eBBz]{Mind Thrust}</strong>&nbsp;Mentally deal 10d10 damage to and fatigue a single target.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.nffP8Mq7rJ8Rskb9]{Mystic Cure}</strong>&nbsp;Restore 12d8 + your Wisdom modifier Hit Points to a living creature or restore life to a recently slain creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.mNHdfIKpF11fhEjo]{Necromantic Revitalization}&nbsp;</strong>Restore hit points to an undead creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.zNSqMd0Tq5JY8hwQ]{Planar Binding}</strong>&nbsp;Trap an extraplanar creature of CR 4 or lower until it performs a task.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.gNgdSyi4pXQmasmc]{Polymorph}&nbsp;</strong>Change the target's shape into that of another creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.w3vQYdl7EZGecOHT]{Polymorph, Mass}&nbsp;</strong>Change multiple target's shapes to that of another creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.Na8z3VijtClCGiZ4]{Read the Flames}&nbsp;</strong>Gives you a single use bonus in the near future.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.HzDlGGxns8iEBHIr]{Reanimate Construct}&nbsp;</strong>This spell turns a destroyed construct into a creature that obeys your spoken commands.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.AHfzMTHx9PI4Z4zn]{Reincarnate}</strong>&nbsp;Bring a target @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.nEJIWMKbPjqKuelo]{Dead} creature back to life in a random body.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.ANDdDHLnY7Dfnhtq]{Remove Radioactivity}</strong>&nbsp;Remove ongoing radiation effects from a creature or object.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.XaWgkqcJcCeQVbnD]{Resistant Armor}</strong>&nbsp;Grant DR 10/&mdash; or energy resistance 10 to three energy types.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.usqy3VusjjgEnM9N]{Restoration}</strong>&nbsp;Restores ability score drain and negative levels.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.bqYL9jEBAU7eqBjf]{Shadow Jump}&nbsp;</strong>Travel through the Shadow Plane to move to a distant shadow.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.NoIRRaiWVr8xxcJX]{Song Of The Cosmos, Greater}&nbsp;</strong>Creatures near you are @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.7PPRS6krnvaTHbxh]{Fascinated} or dazzled for 1d4 rounds.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.rJ0acpj21GDJYaim]{Summon Creature}&nbsp;</strong>This spell summons an extraplanar creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.OM40z8TakmsrvDQU]{Telepathic Bond}</strong>&nbsp;Link allows allies to communicate.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>5th-Level</h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.kzOemsOWuqgbbGZw]{Baleful Polymorph}&nbsp;</strong>Change the target's shape to that of a smaller, weaker creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.11X6d8ptU5SKMUQ0]{Baleful Polymorph, Mass}&nbsp;</strong>Change multiple targets' shapes to that of a smaller, weaker creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.JJYqJxRIOm9EiGtR]{Battlemind Link}&nbsp;</strong>Creates a psychic link that gives a bonus to initiative and other benefits.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.ECQacpm9nCOg31Hy]{Break Enchantment}</strong>&nbsp;Free creatures from curses, enchantments, and transmutations.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.CL7z3gbZwpJtAt0p]{Call Cosmos}</strong>&nbsp;Rain cosmic particles on targets, dealing 4d6 fire damage and 3d6 cold damage.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.fGQnZEijK2SYGnN1]{Command, Greater}</strong> One creature per level obeys select command for 1 round per level.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.4Th6qVd020dWsRPc]{Commune With Planet}&nbsp;</strong>Learn information about the planet you occupy, or about a planet in whose orbit you&rsquo;re within.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.nbpKo7JBQLEfjGCL]{Commune with Nature}</strong>&nbsp;Learn about terrain for 1 mile per level.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.0c25gVm7RKKg1nIy]{Contact Other Plane}</strong>&nbsp;Ask questions of extraplanar entity.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.MZlIC1Y3pWl690LT]{Crush Skull}</strong>&nbsp;Deal 18d8 damage to living creature's head.</p>\n<p><strong>Dismissal:</strong> Force extraplanar creatures whose total CR is no greater than your level + 2 to return to their native planes.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.1FfFraWlxCu1L4rL]{Dispel Magic, Greater}</strong>&nbsp;Cancel multiple spells or effects.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.J14mFZezYHIGHVhO]{Dominate Person}</strong>&nbsp;Control humanoid telepathically.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.wKYmjm8OFwa5L0vX]{Feeblemind}</strong>&nbsp;Target's Intelligence and Charisma scores drop to 1.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.7XJ6x5BZv1k1eBBz]{Mind Thrust}</strong>&nbsp;Mentally deal 15d10 damage to and exhaust one target.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.DcELEg3BAXH3NtsI]{Modify Memory}</strong>&nbsp;Change 5 minutes of target's memories.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.nffP8Mq7rJ8Rskb9]{Mystic Cure}</strong>&nbsp;Restore 16d8 + your Wisdom modifier Hit Points to a living creature or restore life to a recently slain creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.KRxNlIql9Z3ZsTSE]{Mystic Cure, Mass}</strong> Restore 3d8 + your Wisdom modifier Hit Points to one living creature per level.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.mNHdfIKpF11fhEjo]{Necromantic Revitalization}&nbsp;</strong>Restore hit points to an undead creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.zNSqMd0Tq5JY8hwQ]{Planar Binding}</strong>&nbsp;Trap an extraplanar creature of CR 7 or lower until it performs a task.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.gNgdSyi4pXQmasmc]{Polymorph}&nbsp;</strong>Change the target's shape into that of another creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.w3vQYdl7EZGecOHT]{Polymorph, Mass}&nbsp;</strong>Change multiple target's shapes to that of another creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.IRUPIVT101SvIK6l]{Raise Dead}</strong>&nbsp;Restore life to a creature that died no more than 1 day per level ago.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.oK5ksnZnDm9aDOZj]{Reanimate}&nbsp;</strong>Reanimate a recently destroyed construct or undead.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.7BFGmL14AeT9SrA6]{Remove Condition, Greater}</strong>&nbsp;Remove all harmful conditions affecting a creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.D6MCR522HZUBYWSA]{Resistant Aegis}</strong>&nbsp;Grant up to 10 creatures DR 5/&mdash; or energy resistance 5 to all energy types.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.jgLKmk5n9QzQUCNq]{Retrocognition}</strong>&nbsp;Gain psychic impressions of past events in a certain location.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.oEpjvl1MgqsX9Yiv]{Shadow Body}&nbsp;</strong>Merge yourself with the essence of Shadow, giving you great powers for a time.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.rJ0acpj21GDJYaim]{Summon Creature}&nbsp;</strong>This spell summons an extraplanar creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.Enyvti4Zc7DyeRKt]{Synaptic Pulse, Greater}</strong>&nbsp;Stun all creatures within 20 feet for 1d4 rounds.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.Xyo1RrE1atT6Aklc]{Telepathy}</strong>&nbsp;Communicate mentally with any creatures within 100 feet.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.L2YeidH8ae3eGaNR]{Waves of Fatigue}</strong>&nbsp;Several targets become fatigued.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>6th-Level</h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.Avx96qDDFhc6sYOO]{Akashic Revival}&nbsp;</strong>You create perfect documentation of your physical body in the Akashic Record at the time the spell is cast, allowing you to later recall this record and reconstruct your body as it was when you cast this spell.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.kzOemsOWuqgbbGZw]{Baleful Polymorph}&nbsp;</strong>Change the target's shape to that of a smaller, weaker creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.11X6d8ptU5SKMUQ0]{Baleful Polymorph, Mass}&nbsp;</strong>Change multiple targets' shapes to that of a smaller, weaker creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.GXYWlBuSrRRoLogX]{Control Gravity}</strong>&nbsp;Alter gravity in an area.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.t3Bfc9mcAK9NsWbi]{Control Undead}</strong>&nbsp;Undead creatures follow your commands and don't attack you.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.fZJDLIZ0KDrfkZxv]{Enshrining Refuge}</strong>&nbsp;Targets can't attack or be attacked, but can exist comfortably.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.ikKX8lhXOhZRXKpd]{Ethereal Jaunt}</strong>&nbsp;You become ethereal for 1 round per level.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.4GCh1iFm3Wj2aryp]{Flesh to Stone}</strong> Turn a creature into a statue.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.SlMfkSe8xBdhOFFv]{Gravitational Singularity}</strong>&nbsp;Particle with infinite density pulls creatures and objects into it, dealing 12d6 damage each round to those inside.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.xmwEfsAxkVJPLU9B]{Inflict Pain, Mass}</strong>&nbsp;Wracking pain imposes -2 penalty to ability checks, attack rolls, and skill checks on one target per level.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.iyN2Ssp0ggbriwY0]{Mind Swap}&nbsp;</strong>Swap your mind with the target.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.7XJ6x5BZv1k1eBBz]{Mind Thrust}</strong>&nbsp;Mentally deal 17d10 damage to, exhaust, and stun one target.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.nffP8Mq7rJ8Rskb9]{Mystic Cure}</strong>&nbsp;Restore 20d8 + your Wisdom modifier HP to a living creature or restore life to a recently slain creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.KRxNlIql9Z3ZsTSE]{Mystic Cure, Mass}</strong>&nbsp;Restore 5d8 + your Wisdom modifier Hit Points to one living creature per level.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.mNHdfIKpF11fhEjo]{Necromantic Revitalization}&nbsp;</strong>Restore hit points to an undead creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.FUJiXbrtJSqQK9JO]{Planar Barrier}</strong>&nbsp;Seal an area against all planar travel into or within it.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.zNSqMd0Tq5JY8hwQ]{Planar Binding}</strong>&nbsp;Trap an extraplanar creature of CR 10 or lower until it performs a task.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.yjClpQv6CCrRE4EC]{Plane Shift}</strong>&nbsp;As many as eight creatures travel to another plane you choose.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.gNgdSyi4pXQmasmc]{Polymorph}&nbsp;</strong>Change the target's shape into that of another creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.w3vQYdl7EZGecOHT]{Polymorph, Mass}&nbsp;</strong>Change multiple target's shapes to that of another creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.oeaAybyT4rKFPfIr]{Psychic Surgery}</strong> Cure all Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma damage and drain, plus remove other mental afflictions and conditions.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.9Jk5eas4Zz0Sd0LL]{Regenerate}</strong>&nbsp;Grow back target's severed limbs, restore 12d8 Hit Points, and remove exhaustion and fatigue.</p>\n<p><strong>Resistant Armor, Greater:</strong> Grant DR 15/&mdash; or energy resistance 15 against four energy types.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.o78PjAYBWQpiHwMK]{Shadow Walk}</strong>&nbsp;Step into a shadowy realm to travel to a destination rapidly.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.RFUcWmXg7jgKO1ZT]{Snuff Life}</strong>&nbsp;Instantly kill or massively damage one creature per 2 caster levels, depending on targets' CRs.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.SSEw9AIr2K5w5jlg]{Star Storm}&nbsp;</strong>Hailing plasma deals 6d8 electricity damage and 6d8 fire damage to creatures and objects in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.IoR7MUe920ta3DzM]{Subjective Reality}</strong>&nbsp;You convince yourself one creature or object is an illusion.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.gRv9eLrl4VCO825Z]{Suggestion, Mass}</strong>&nbsp;Compel one target per level to follow stated course of action.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.rJ0acpj21GDJYaim]{Summon Creature}&nbsp;</strong>This spell summons an extraplanar creature.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.rJqk12KW4phqFpI5]{Summon Drift Beacons}&nbsp;</strong>You conjure several Drift beacons into your current star system.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.ekj93MeLRazilGH5]{Telepathic Jaunt}</strong>&nbsp;Use your telepathic bond with a creature to teleport to its location.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.VvCP8MdSZtXREp2x]{True Seeing}</strong>&nbsp;Target can see things as they really are.</p>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.YnRDHb216HdROPeo]{Vision}</strong>&nbsp;Answer a question about a person, place, or object.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>No Level</h2>\n<p><strong>@Compendium[sfrpg.spells.i3lpfndXeLq85h12]{Miracle}&nbsp;</strong>Alter reality to better suit you.</p>","flags":{},"folder":"","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","permission":{"QqVQDajn5ZN4kl25":3,"default":0}}
{"_id":"6OLO3qLTaAenICUz","name":"Urban Terrain","content":"<p>&gt;@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.lRtz3KadYxtrd5qS]{Biomes}</p>\n<p>Source: CRB pg. 397</p>\n<p>Urban terrain can be found in most settlements where the people have greatly exerted their influence over the surrounding environment, constructing buildings where they can live and work in comfort and laying well-defined roads, usually paved. This type of terrain can occur in just about any biome, and it often supersedes the environmental effects of that biome. Urban terrain can include space stations, and it is often replete with technology. The most common rules sections to reference when using urban terrain are @Compendium[sfrpg.rules.TN4VeY75Z2Ce8IT7]{Settlements} (see page 405), @Compendium[sfrpg.rules.CPkDG7SXnJ0ky8px]{Structures} (see page 406), and Vehicles (see page 228), as well as @Compendium[sfrpg.rules.zDW0cDPQL55G7ose]{Breaking Objects} (see page 409) and sometimes @Compendium[sfrpg.rules.QHtKixa59DI9xQfO]{Radiation} (see page 403).</p>\n<h3>Stealth And Detection In Urban Terrain</h3>\n<p>In a settlement with wide, open streets, the maximum distance at which a creature can succeed at a Perception check to detect the presence of others is 2d6×10 feet. In a settlement where the buildings are more crowded, standing close together, this distance is 1d6×10 feet. The presence of crowds might reduce this distance.<br /><br />Thanks to twisting side streets and vehicles that can provide cover, it’s usually easy for a creature to use Stealth to hide in a settlement. In addition, settlements are often noisy, making Perception checks that rely on sound more difficult, usually increasing the DC of the check at the GM’s discretion.</p>","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
