px; width: 28px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\"><small>&mdash;</small></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px; background-color: #c2e0f4;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 360px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.equipment.heDMhwIJvOPQvz9a]{Streetsweeper, LFD}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 32px;\">12</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 49px;\">39,300</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 51px;\">3d10 So</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 38px;\">50 ft.</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 73px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.O5GDQUKPCJ9Zbnfj]{Knockdown}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\">40 charges</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 37px;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 28px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\"><small>Boost 1d8</small></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 360px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.equipment.aWKUxoZGcZBS7zc4]{Sonic rifle, HFD}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 32px;\">14</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 49px;\">80,200</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 51px;\">4d10 So</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 38px;\">50 ft.</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 73px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.O5GDQUKPCJ9Zbnfj]{Deafen}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\">80 charges</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 37px;\">4</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 28px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\"><small>&mdash;</small></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px; background-color: #c2e0f4;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 360px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.equipment.5pCXYCxOalCVBMvu]{Streetsweeper, HFD}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 32px;\">16</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 49px;\">195,000</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 51px;\">5d10 So</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 38px;\">50 ft.</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 73px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.O5GDQUKPCJ9Zbnfj]{Knockdown}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\">40 charges</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 37px;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 28px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\"><small>Boost 1d10</small></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 360px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.equipment.x4uktPtMgNGJeI5A]{Sonic rifle, banshee}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 32px;\">18</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 49px;\">364,500</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 51px;\">6d10 So</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 38px;\">50 ft.</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 73px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.O5GDQUKPCJ9Zbnfj]{Deafen}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\">100 charges</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 37px;\">5</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 28px;\">2</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\"><small>&mdash;</small></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px; background-color: #34495e;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 833px; color: #ffffff;\" colspan=\"10\"><strong>UNCATEGORIZED</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px; background-color: #c2e0f4;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 360px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.equipment.ksxWNthDyNPTIqtN]{Needler Rifle}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 32px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 49px;\">110</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 51px;\">1d6 P</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 38px;\">60 ft.</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 73px;\">@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.O5GDQUKPCJ9Zbnfj]{Injection DC +2}</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\">12 darts</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 37px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 28px;\">1</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px; width: 60px;\"><small>Analog, injection</small></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","flags":{},"folder":"","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","permission":{"EgDbkW0aYa1c3C2f":3,"default":0}}
{"_id":"aKqRtg165rAly1Cc","name":"Poisons","content":"<p><sub><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">Source </span><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">Starfinder Core Rulebook pg. 415</span></sub></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">&gt;</span><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">@Compendium[sfrpg.rules.JaRMioj4isNp7r1P]{Afflictions}</span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">Each poison has a delivery mechanism. A character who is poisoned attempts a saving throw after the listed onset and at the listed frequency thereafter. Upon initial exposure, regardless of whether she succeeds at her saving throw, the victim loses a number of Hit Points equal to the poison&rsquo;s DC &ndash; 10. If a victim is exposed to multiple doses of the same poison, she must attempt a separate save for each dose and progresses to the next state on the poison track with each failed save. </span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 class=\"framing\">Strength Poison Track</h1>\n<p><strong>Healthy&mdash;Weakened&mdash;Impaired&mdash;Staggered&mdash;Immobile&mdash;Dead</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Weakened</h3>\n<p>The victim takes a &ndash;2 penalty to Strength-based ability checks, attack rolls, damage rolls, and skill checks, and the DCs of his spells and special abilities decrease by 2. The victim&rsquo;s total carrying capacity is reduced by two-thirds (minimum 1 bulk), and he gains the @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.OwZA6flUQPH0jPA0]{Encumbered} condition regardless of how much he is carrying.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Impaired</h3>\n<p>The victim takes an additional &ndash;2 penalty to the affected checks, rolls, and DCs, and he gains the @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.11k3ObUIXEYFGrg9]{Overburdened} condition regardless of how much he is carrying.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Staggered</h3>\n<p>The victim is @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.aAQ6SW6iK0EVq8Ce]{Staggered}, except he can still take a purely mental full action.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Immobile</h3>\n<p>The victim is @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.RxvbSB9ZgSCBu2jw]{Helpless} and can take only purely mental actions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Dead</h3>\n<p>The victim <span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">@Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.nEJIWMKbPjqKuelo]{Dies}</span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 class=\"framing\">Dexterity Poison Track</h1>\n<p><strong>Healthy&mdash;Sluggish&mdash;Stiffened&mdash;Staggered&mdash;Immobile&mdash;Dead</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Sluggish</h3>\n<p>The victim takes a &ndash;2 penalty to Reflex saves and Dexterity-based ability checks, attack rolls, and skill checks; the DCs of her spells and special abilities decrease by 2; and she becomes @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.MZ8OoH1GE9qDMyCD]{Flat-Footed}.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Stiffened</h3>\n<p>The victim loses her Dexterity bonus to her Armor Class, and she can&rsquo;t take reactions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Staggered</h3>\n<p>The victim is @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.aAQ6SW6iK0EVq8Ce]{Staggered} but can take purely mental full actions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Immobile</h3>\n<p>The victim is @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.RxvbSB9ZgSCBu2jw]{Helpless} and can take only purely mental actions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Dead</h3>\n<p>The victim <span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">@Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.nEJIWMKbPjqKuelo]{Dies}</span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 class=\"framing\">Constitution Poison Track</h1>\n<p><strong>Healthy&mdash;Weakened&mdash;Impaired&mdash;Debilitated&mdash;Unconscious&mdash;Dead</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Weakened</h3>\n<p>The victim takes a &ndash;2 penalty to Fortitude saves, Constitution checks, and Constitution-based DCs. Every time the victim attempts a Fortitude save against the poison&mdash;whether he succeeds or fails&mdash;he loses Hit Points as per on initial exposure.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Impaired</h3>\n<p>The victim takes an additional &ndash;2 penalty to the affected checks, and the DCs of his spells and special abilities decrease by 2.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Debilitated</h3>\n<p>Strenuous actions cause the victim pain. If he takes a standard action, he immediately loses 1 Hit Point.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Unconscious</h3>\n<p>The victim is @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.lf8pbezocjYIvR9y]{Unconscious} and can&rsquo;t be woken by any means.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Dead</h3>\n<p>The victim <span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">@Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.nEJIWMKbPjqKuelo]{Dies}</span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 class=\"framing\">Intelligence Poison Track</h1>\n<p><strong>Healthy&mdash;Weakened&mdash;Impaired&mdash;Animalistic&mdash;Comatose&mdash;Dead</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Weakened</h3>\n<p>The victim takes a &ndash;2 penalty to all Intelligence-based ability checks and skill checks, and the DCs of her spells and special abilities decrease by 2. If she has 1 or more levels in a spellcasting class whose key ability score is Intelligence, she can&rsquo;t cast her highest level of spells from that class.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Impaired</h3>\n<p>The victim takes an additional &ndash;2 penalty to the affected checks and the affected DCs decrease by an additional 2. If she has 1 or more levels in a spellcasting class whose key ability score is Intelligence, she can&rsquo;t cast her 2 highest levels of spells from that class.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Animalistic</h3>\n<p>The victim suffers the effects of a @Compendium[sfrpg.spells.wKYmjm8OFwa5L0vX]{Feeblemind} spell, except her Charisma and Charisma-based skills are unaffected.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Comatose</h3>\n<p>The victim can&rsquo;t process thoughts and can&rsquo;t be woken.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Dead</h3>\n<p>The victim&rsquo;s brain stops working, and she <span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">@Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.nEJIWMKbPjqKuelo]{Dies}</span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 class=\"framing\">Wisdom Poison Track</h1>\n<p><strong>Healthy&mdash;Weakened&mdash;Impaired&mdash;Confused&mdash;Comatose&mdash;Dead</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Weakened</h3>\n<p>The victim takes a &ndash;2 penalty to Will saves and Wisdom-based ability checks and skill checks, and the DCs of his spells and special abilities decrease by 2. If he has 1 or more levels in a spellcasting class whose key ability score is Wisdom, he can&rsquo;t cast his highest level of spells from that class.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Impaired</h3>\n<p>The victim takes an additional &ndash;2 penalty to the affected checks, and the affected DCs decrease by an additional 2. If he has 1 or more levels in a spellcasting class whose key ability score is Wisdom, he can&rsquo;t cast his 2 highest levels of spells from that class.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Confused</h3>\n<p>The victim gains the @Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.8rIj0ewW4bL8Uph5]{Confused} condition.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Comatose</h3>\n<p>The victim can&rsquo;t experience reality and can&rsquo;t be woken.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Dead</h3>\n<p>The victim&rsquo;s brain stops working, and he <span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">@Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.nEJIWMKbPjqKuelo]{Dies}</span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 class=\"framing\">Charisma Poison Track</h1>\n<p><strong>Healthy&mdash;Weakened&mdash;Impaired&mdash;Pliable&mdash;Catatonic&mdash;Dead</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Weakened</h3>\n<p>The victim takes a &ndash;2 penalty to Charisma-based ability checks and skill checks, and the DCs of her spells and special abilities decrease by 2. If she has 1 or more levels in a spellcasting class whose key ability score is Charisma, she can&rsquo;t cast her highest level of spells from that class.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Impaired</h3>\n<p>The victim takes an additional &ndash;2 penalty to the affected checks and DCs. If she has 1 or more levels in a spellcasting class whose key ability score is Charisma, she can&rsquo;t cast her 2 highest levels of spells from that class.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Pliable</h3>\n<p>The victim has little sense of self and goes along with nearly any order or suggestion. Creatures attempting Bluff, Diplomacy, or Intimidate checks against her automatically succeed, though Diplomacy checks to improve her attitude still have the normal DC.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Catatonic</h3>\n<p>The victim loses agency and can&rsquo;t interact with anything.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Dead</h3>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">The victim loses autonomic functions and </span><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\"><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">@Compendium[sfrpg.conditions.nEJIWMKbPjqKuelo]{Dies}</span>. </span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 class=\"framing\">Drugs</h2>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DetailedOutput\">Drugs are a special kind of poison that grant a beneficial effect right away but also move the user a single step down the associated poison track. However, the user doesn&rsquo;t lose Hit Points, even if the drug functions as a Constitution poison. Taking a drug also exposes the user to the addiction disease (see page 418), with a DC that depends on how addictive the drug is. If a character is dosed with a drug against his will, he can attempt a Fortitude save against the @Compendium[sfrpg.rules.aKqRtg165rAly1Cc]{Drug}&rsquo;s DC. If he succeeds, this negates both the drug&rsquo;s beneficial and negative effects, as well the chance for addiction. Immunity to poison or a similar effect prevents a character from experiencing the drug&rsquo;s beneficial effects, and removing or suppressing a drug&rsquo;s negative effects with restorative spells also cancels the benefits.</span></p>","flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg"}
